: rgb(64, 64, 64); text-decoration: underline;">An Investor's Introduction =
to Urbit - Part 1</a></strong></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-=
size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><em>By Basho</em></p><b=
lockquote style=3D"border-left: 4px solid #51b4e9; margin: 20px 0; padding:=
 0;"><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px=
; margin: 0 0 20px 0; margin-left: 20px;"><em>Urbit is a personal computer =
that runs in the cloud and natively combines a unique identity (in the form=
 of an NFT), data storage (via an integrated database), application executi=
on (which is run server-side, i.e. by the individual user) and P2P networki=
ng. The result is a system in which users control all of their own data and=
 applications, and can easily interact with all other users on the network =
without reliance on centralized companies.</em></p></blockquote><div class=
